register.name: CNTFRQ_EL0
register.description: This register is provided so that software can discover the frequency of the system counter. It must be programmed with this value as part of system initialization. The value of the register is not interpreted by hardware.

register.name: CNTHCTL_EL2
register.description: Controls the generation of an event stream from the physical counter, and access from Non-secure EL1 to the physical counter and the Non-secure EL1 physical timer.

bitField.name: EVNTI
bitField.description: Selects which bit (0 to 15) of the counter register CNTPCT_EL0 is the trigger for the event stream generated from that counter, when that stream is enabled.

bitField.name: EVNTDIR
bitField.description: Controls which transition of the counter register CNTPCT_EL0 trigger bit, defined by EVNTI, generates an event when the event stream is enabled:

bitField.name: EVNTEN
bitField.description: Enables the generation of an event stream from the counter register CNTPCT_EL0:

bitField.name: EL1PCEN
bitField.description: Traps Non-secure EL0 and EL1 accesses to the physical timer registers to EL2.

bitField.name: EL1PCTEN
bitField.description: Traps Non-secure EL0 and EL1 accesses to the physical counter register to EL2.

register.name: CNTHP_CTL_EL2
register.gui_name: Counter-timer Hypervisor Physical Timer Control register
register.description: Control register for the EL2 physical timer.

bitField.name: ISTATUS
bitField.description: The status of the timer.

bitField.name: IMASK
bitField.description: Timer interrupt mask bit.

bitField.name: ENABLE
bitField.description: Enables the timer.

register.name: CNTHP_CVAL_EL2
register.gui_name: Counter-timer Hypervisor Physical Timer CompareValue register
register.description: Holds the compare value for the EL2 physical timer.

bitField.name: CompareValue
bitField.description: Holds the EL2 physical timer CompareValue.

register.name: CNTHP_TVAL_EL2
register.gui_name: Counter-timer Hypervisor Physical Timer TimerValue register
register.description: Holds the timer value for the EL2 physical timer.

bitField.name: TimerValue
bitField.description: The TimerValue view of the EL2 physical timer.

register.name: CNTKCTL_EL1
register.description: Controls the generation of an event stream from the virtual counter, and access from EL0 to the physical counter, virtual counter, EL1 physical timers, and the virtual timer.

bitField.name: EL0PTEN
bitField.description: Traps EL0 accesses to the physical timer registers to EL1.

bitField.name: EL0VTEN
bitField.description: Traps EL0 accesses to the virtual timer registers to EL1.

bitField.name: EVNTI
bitField.description: Selects which bit (0 to 15) of the counter register CNTVCT_EL0 is the trigger for the event stream generated from that counter, when that stream is enabled.

bitField.name: EVNTDIR
bitField.description: Controls which transition of the counter register CNTVCT_EL0 trigger bit, defined by EVNTI, generates an event when the event stream is enabled:

bitField.name: EVNTEN
bitField.description: Enables the generation of an event stream from the counter register CNTVCT_EL0:

bitField.name: EL0VCTEN
bitField.description: Traps EL0 accesses to the frequency register and virtual counter register to EL1.

bitField.name: EL0PCTEN
bitField.description: Traps EL0 accesses to the frequency register and physical counter register to EL1.

register.name: CNTPS_CTL_EL1
register.gui_name: Counter-timer Physical Secure Timer Control register
register.description: Control register for the secure physical timer, usually accessible at EL3 but configurably accessible at EL1 in Secure state.

bitField.name: ISTATUS
bitField.description: The status of the timer.

bitField.name: IMASK
bitField.description: Timer interrupt mask bit.

bitField.name: ENABLE
bitField.description: Enables the timer.

register.name: CNTPS_CVAL_EL1
register.gui_name: Counter-timer Physical Secure Timer CompareValue register
register.description: Holds the compare value for the secure physical timer, usually accessible at EL3 but configurably accessible at EL1 in Secure state.

bitField.name: CompareValue
bitField.description: Holds the secure physical timer CompareValue.

register.name: CNTPS_TVAL_EL1
register.gui_name: Counter-timer Physical Secure Timer TimerValue register
register.description: Holds the timer value for the secure physical timer, usually accessible at EL3 but configurably accessible at EL1 in Secure state.

bitField.name: TimerValue
bitField.description: The TimerValue view of the secure physical timer.

register.name: CNTP_CTL_EL0
register.description: Control register for the EL1 physical timer.

bitField.name: ENABLE
bitField.description: Enables the timer.

register.name: CNTP_CVAL_EL0
register.description: Holds the compare value for the EL1 physical timer.

bitField.name: CompareValue
bitField.description: Holds the EL1 physical timer CompareValue.

register.name: CNTP_TVAL_EL0
register.description: Holds the timer value for the EL1 physical timer.

bitField.name: TimerValue
bitField.description: The TimerValue view of the EL1 physical timer.

register.name: CNTVCT_EL0
register.description: Holds the 64-bit virtual count value. The virtual count value is equal to the physical count value visible in CNTPCT_EL0 minus the virtual offset visible in CNTVOFF_EL2.

register.name: CNTVOFF_EL2
register.description: Holds the 64-bit virtual offset. This is the offset between the physical count value visible in CNTPCT_EL0 and the virtual count value visible in CNTVCT_EL0.

register.name: CNTV_CTL_EL0
register.description: Control register for the virtual timer.

bitField.name: ISTATUS

bitField.name: ENABLE
bitField.description: Enables the timer.

register.name: CNTV_CVAL_EL0
register.description: Holds the compare value for the virtual timer.

bitField.name: CompareValue
bitField.description: Holds the EL1 virtual timer CompareValue.

register.name: CNTV_TVAL_EL0
register.description: Holds the timer value for the EL1 virtual timer.

bitField.name: TimerValue
bitField.description: The TimerValue view of the EL1 virtual timer.
